/-
  Linen.Data.Colour.Names — names for colours

  ## Haskell equivalent
  `Data.Colour.Names` from https://hackage.haskell.org/package/colour

  ## Design
  Names taken from the SVG 1.1 specification
  (<http://www.w3.org/TR/SVG11/types.html#ColorKeywords>). `black` is
  re-exported from `Data.Colour.Internal` rather than redefined, matching
  upstream. `readColourName`, upstream a polymorphic `MonadFail m => String
  -> m (Colour a)` (so it can fail as `Maybe`, `[]`, `IO`, …), is ported
  concretely as `String → Option Colour`, Lean's idiomatic shape for a
  lookup that can fail; callers wanting another failure representation can
  trivially convert from `Option`.
-/
